<p>There are two approaches to calculating gates with inputs in superposition.</p>

<p>The first is to calculate by multiplying the state vector and gate matrix.</p>

<p><image source="GeneralNOT.png" width="50%" /></p>

<p>The second is to apply the operation to each bit in the ket, then reorganize the result.</p>

<p><image source="GeneralNOT2.png" width="40%" /></p>

<p> Try this yourself with the SWAP gate with the starting state:</p>

